[SN]TITLE[SN]
SNP's John Swinney at helm of raucous FMQs

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Scotland's Deputy First Minister John Swinney took the helm of a raucous FMQs at Holyrood.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
9 March 2017 Last updated at 15:32 GMT
He tackled opposition questions on the prospects of a second Scottish independence referendum and the state of the oil and gas industry.
First Minister Nicola Sturgeon was not available for her weekly Q&A because she was in London at the launch of a memorial dedicated to those who served in the Afghanistan and Iraq wars.
